commitResults.messageTitle: Fix for bug caused by delete command
commitResults.messageBody:
When a Participant is deleted from Managera using the delete command, it
is removed from the Participant list but not from any events that the
Participant was previously attending.

Hence, when Managera is restarted, it still attempts to restore the now
missing Participant object in the event(s). This causes Managera to not
start up at all.

Let's add references to any events in the Participant class so that when
a Participant object is deleted, we can remove any references to this
object in the events the Participant was attending. These references are
restored on startup when the Event objects are restored from the save
file. The event references are not stored in the save file.

* Add a list of events as an attribute to Participant class.
* Fix the bug causing Managera to not start after a Participant of an
  event is deleted.
* Changes to certain methods which violate Law of Demeter.
* Add test cases for new methods to add and remove event references from
  Participant objects.
* Update user guide as some command syntax are outdated.

commitResults.messageTitle: Remove instance of Law of Demeter violation
Resolve issue with double Participant objects
commitResults.messageBody:
Upon startup, Managera would create up to two instances of each
Participant. One instance is added into addressbook, and the other is
added into the Participant list of any event the Participant is
attending. This is due to an outdated method of deserialising the
Participant and Event objects from the save file.

This causes unneccessary usage of extra memory to store the extra
Participant objects.

Let's adjust the way that Managera deserialises the Participant and
Event objects from the save file so that only one Participant object
is ever created for each Participant.

commitResults.messageTitle: Fix UI bug for events not updating participants
commitResults.messageBody:
When Participants are added to or removed from an Event, the Event in
the Event list of Managera does not update its list of Participants
correctly. This is due to how ObservableList works, which listens to
changes in the objects in the list, but not when the attributes of the
objects are changed.

Let's change the list of Participants in Events from an ArrayList to an
ObservableList, and include a callback in UniqueEventList to listen for
any changes made to this ObservableList in the Event. That way, when a
Participant is removed from or added to an Event, it would invoke the
callback method and cause javaFX to update the UI accordingly.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add feature to view a Participant's details
commitResults.messageBody:
Let's add a new feature to Managera to allow users to search for
a Participant using their participantId and view their details. If the
user's input is not precise enough and there are multiple participantIds
that match, these IDs will be displayed to the user so that he may
refine his search.

Let's add:
* A view command to allow users to find a Participant by their
  participantId and view the Participant's details.
* Update user guide to reflect this new feature.
* Fix issues with the user guide regarding broken hyperlinks and
  outdated syntax.
* Add test files for the newly added classes: ViewCommand,
  ViewCommandParser, ParticipantIdMatchesGivenIdPredicate. (100% line
  coverage)
* Add an additional test for AddCommandTest to provide coverage for
  toString method.

I realised that with my previous implementation, the user would
encounter an issue if there are at least two participants where one
participant's ID is contained within the other. The user would never be
able to narrow down his search to the former. The implementation has
been adjusted to fix that issue, but the command will no longer list the
similar IDs as with the previous implementation.

commitResults.messageBody:
Marking an event as done creates a new Event object. Hence, any
participants for this event will still contain a reference to the old
uncompleted event.

Let's:
* Change the implementation of done command so that it just modifies the
  done status of the event instead of instantiating a new instance.
* Change the isDone attribute of Event class to a BooleanProperty, which
  is Observable. This is so that the UI updates accordingly when an
  event is marked as done.
* Adjust the implementation of the execute method in DoneEventCommand to
  reduce coupling with Model.

View command uses participantId to find the specific participant, but
this adds little value as it only searches within the filtered list. It
would be enough (and easier for the user) to just use the displayed
index to view the Participant.

The view command currently is also not very useful as the ParticipantCard
already displays most of the details of the Participant.

The doneEvent command can be jsut simplified to just `done` as it is an
Event-specific command.

Let's:
* Change view command to use index to perform the search instead.
* Give view command the ability to show the events that the Participant
  is attending. This will give value to the view command.
* Adjust the test files to accomodate the changes above.
* Change the command word of the done command.
* Change the implementation of done command so that it aligns with
  existing implementations better.
